/> </mxCell> <mxCell id="a5Bq1GeSvkBcT2mBl7S9-161" value="<b>Definitions:</b><br><ul><li>Audit selection criteria:</li><ul><li><i>Inconsistencies</i>: Are there any inconsistencies in the data?</li><li><i>Score4to5</i>: positive performance evaluation, but with a score between 4 and 5.</li><li><i>Highlow</i>: very high score on one block <i>of indicators</i> and very low on the rest (especially if the fact that they score very high on that block influences their positive performance evaluation)</li><li><i>Suggestion</i>: audit requests have been received in the suggestion box</li><li><i>Diversity</i>: diversity of legal entity types and typologies of organisations. In this sense, small, medium and large organisations will be more likely to receive audits than micro-enterprises (less than 5 working members).</li></ul><li>Documentation:</li><ul><li><i>Block:</i>&nbsp;category of documentation. Eg general data, economy and profit policy, equity and democracy, environmental sustainability, social commitment and cooperation, and quality of work.</li></ul></ul><span style="font-size: 12px"><br></span><b>Modelling rationale</b><ul><li>Audit selection criteria are considered per organisation. Hence, audit selection criteria table is attached to each organisation.</li><li>According to documentation, In the case that the audited organisation needs to redo their social balance, the results of the new performance evaluation will be checked by the Social Balance Advisory Committee. Exact steps of that procedure are unclear, so. It is assumed that that is a different process, so audit process ends after informing organisation of redo.&nbsp;</li><li><i>Block&nbsp;</i>attribute under documentation. In method documentation, non exhaustive list is given for this attribute. Hence, text data type is used.</li></ul><div><b>Constraints</b><ul><li>Enumerated data types:</li><ul><li>Audit selection criterion.type: Inconsistencies, score between 4 and 5, high or low, suggested, diversity</li></ul><li><span style="text-align: center">An Organisation can only be picked once per campaign for an audit.</span><br></li></ul></div><div><b><b>Improvements and things to complete:</b></b></div><div><ul><li>Validation by Sergio.</li></ul></div><div><b>Doubts:</b><br><ul><li>Actor of step 1, 3 and 4 are unclear.</li><li>Not sure of difference between SB Committee and SB <mxCell id="0" /> <mxCell id="1" parent="0" /> <mxCell id="UAYppWUT7ZeBG5gpeuXI-1" value="<b>Some definitions:</b><br><ul><li>A <i>social agent</i> is a regional network; i.e. an association of organisations that are from the same region (<i>XES</i>, in Catalonia, and <i>REAS-PV </i>in the Valencian Community). All networks belong to a 2nd-level network called <i>REAS Red de Redes</i>, which is not modelled.<br></li><li>I refer as <i>Sectorial network</i> to an association of organisations that are from the same sector (e.g. <i>Table of Ethical Finance -Mesa de Finanzas Eticas</i>-, <i>AERESS</i>). The original name in Spanish (<i>ámbito de pertenencia</i>) has no good translation into English. <br></li><li>A <i>module</i> refers to an ESEA method or to an ESEA method variant; some current modules are Social Balance-Full, Social balance-Basic, Community balance-Full, Community balance-Basic. There are more.</li><li><i>Contact type</i> is a stakeholder group (e.g. workers, clients)<br></li></ul><b>Modelling rationale</b><ul><li><i>Organisations provide data</i> represents the execution of several instances of the process in the right-hand side.</li><li>Many attributes referring to user interface labels (e.g. Question.Name) have one value per language, but we have ignored this for the sake of simplicity.</li><li><i>Avg last campaign</i> actually has 3 values, one per gender identities (women, men, other), but we just included one attribute for the sake of simplicity.</li><li>W.r.t. the relationship between <i>Social agent </i>and <i>Autonomous community</i>, although the tool allows a many to many relationship 0..M --- 0..M, in practice it is a one to one 0..1 --- 1..1.</li></ul><div><b>Constraints</b><ul><li>A given <i>Question</i> (having its <i>Id</i>) may have different data (e.g. <i>Name</i>, <i>Description</i>, etc.) in different <i>Campaign</i>s. It is as if the primary key of <i>Question</i> was <i>Question.Id</i> and <i>Campaign.Name</i>.</li><li>Enumerated data types:</li><ul><li><i><span></span>Question.Data type</i>={<i>short text, long text, integer gender, real gender, integer, real, yes/no, range, checkbox list, radiobutton list, dropdown list, literal</i>}; <i>range</i> is a 1-10 Likert scale; <i>literal</i> indicates that it is not a question or indicator, but a text fragment in the middle of a survey.</li><li><i>Question.Unit</i>={<i>Euro, Persons</i>, ...}</li><li><i>YesNo.Value</i>={"Si", "No"}, which correspond to yes and no, respectively<br></li></ul><li>Only questions with <i>Data type</i> is either <i>checkbox list</i>, <i>radiobutton list</i>, or <i>dropdown list</i>,can be associated to a <i>List.</i></li><li><i>Response</i>s only need a <i>Respondent</i> (i.e.<i> Response.resp</i>!=null) when the <i>Response</i> corresponds to a <i>Question</i> of a <i>Submodule</i>. If it corresponds to a <i>Question</i> of a <i>Parent module</i>, then the respondent is assumed to be the user who is <i>admin_user</i> for that <i>Organisation</i>.</li><li>During activities <i>SB-XES.NET.03. SB helpdesk offers support to organisations</i> and <i>SB-XES.NET.05. SB coordinator performs technical validation</i>, any piece of data produced during <i>SB-XES.BAL.01. Accountant fills internal survey</i>&nbsp; can be edited by the network coordinator. Additionally, <i>SB-XES.NET.05. SB coordinator performs technical validation </i>sets the status to <i>Technically validated.</i><br></li><li><i>Indicator value</i> is created either on demand or after the accountant has submitted the data or any later update to the account is made. The values (<i>Indicator value.Value</i>) are calculated automatically, based on the survey responses (<i>Response.Value</i>) and the <i>Indicator.Formula</i>.</li><li>During activity <i>SB-XES.NET.02. SB coordinator starts data collection stage</i>, the network coordinator makes sure that all organisations that have requested doing the social balance, have been either approved or rejected (which is done via <i>SB-XES.ORG.02. SB coordinator evaluates request</i>).</li><li>During activity <i>SB-XES.NET.04. SB coordinator closes data collection stage</i>, the network coordinator makes sure that all organisations that had requested&nbsp;doing the social balance have finished (and therefore they have submitted the balance data via <i>SB-XES.BAL.04. Accountant submits data</i>). Otherwise, she can manually change the <i>Balance.Status</i> to <i>Completed</i> or (if she wants to get rid of unfinished balances) she can also manually set the status to <i>Rejected</i>.<br></li></ul></div><div><div><b><b>Improvements and things to complete:</b><br></b><ul><li>The generation of documents (Excel sheets, reports, infographics, labels) happens some activities; see examples next. However, the moments when the documents are generated are actually configured in the tool (during<i> SB-XES.NET.01. SB coordinator configures campaign</i>), so this could change. <br></li><ul><li>Accountants can download Excel sheets after <i>SB-XES.NET.05. SB coordinator performs technical validation</i>.&nbsp;</li><li>Accountants can download the balance report and the label image after <i>SB-XES.NET.07. SB committee evaluates organisations</i>. <br></li><li>Accountants can download the infographic after <i>SB-XES.NET.07. SB committee evaluates organisations</i>, if they are members of XES (or, if not, when they pay a small fee for it).<br></li></ul></ul><b>Doubts:</b><br><ul><li>Modules and networks</li><ul><li>Do all fields apply to children modules; e.g. <i><i>Question guide </i>(Guía de preguntas</i>), <i>Data privacy policy</i> (<i>Documento de política de confidencialidad</i>). These only seem to be applicable to parent modules.</li><li>Can an organisation that is established in an <i>Autonomous community</i>, belong to a <i>Social agent</i> (<i>agente social</i>) that does not operate in that region?<br></li><li>Can an organisation that belongs to a <i>Social agent</i> (<i>agente social</i>) request access to all modules in the tool or only those that the network offers?<br></li></ul><li>Campaigns<br></li><ul><li>What information does a campaign consist of? E.g. start date, deadline for data collection. And which of these pieces of info are stored in the tool? Who defines these? Are these dates the same for all regional networks?<br></li><li>How are campaigns managed? Do the networks specify the dates of the campaigns themselves? <br></li><li>Are the stages of the campaign automatically activated in the tool based on the campaign info or do the SB coordinators have to open and close the data collection stage.</li></ul><li>Validation rules</li><ul><li>How are validation rules executed? What happens when a validation rule is executed and it is not complied with?</li><li>We have some comments w.r.t. validation rules:<br></li><ul><li>E.g.
